'''Changshou Lake''' ({{Zh|s=长寿湖|t=長壽湖|p=Chángshòu Hú}}) is a man-made [[lake]] with another name Shizitun (Lion Beach) [[Reservoir]] in [[Changshou District|Changshou]], [[Chongqing]], [[China]]. In the purpose of generating electric power, four [[hydraulic power station]]s were built after the [[dam]] construction had been completed in the 1950s. Since then a state farm was set up for [[fishery]] and [[horticulture]] as well as [[animal husbandry]]. Its surface area is 60&nbsp;km² with an irrigation area amounting to 248&nbsp;km². There are many [[islands]] within the lake, good for tourism.
