'''Johns Hopkins Aramco Healthcare''' is a joint project between [[Saudi Aramco]], energy and integrated global petrochemicals company, and [[Johns Hopkins School of Medicine]], the academic medical teaching and research arm of [[Johns Hopkins University]].  It is intended to provide healthcare for the employees of Saudi Aramco and their families.  It is jointly owned by the company and the university.<ref>{{cite news|title=Johns Hopkins Medicine, Saudi Arabia oil giant set to launch joint venture|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/baltimore/news/2014/01/28/johns-hopkins-saudi-aramco-partnership.html|accessdate=3 September 2015|publisher=Baltimore Business Journal|date=28 January 2014}}</ref>

