{{BLP sources|date=April 2017}} {{Infobox scientist |image = José Narro Robles.jpg |image_size = 220px | | name = José Narro Robles | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1948|12|05}} | birth_place = [[Saltillo, Coahuila]], [[Mexico]]. | residence = [[Mexico City]] | nationality = Mexican | field = [[Healthcare]], [[Medicine]] and [[Higher Education]] | work_institution = [[National Autonomous University of Mexico]] | alma_mater = [[National Autonomous University of Mexico]], [[University of Birmingham]] | doctoral_advisor = | known_for = [[Dean (education)|Dean]] of the National Autonomous University of Mexico | awards = | footnotes = }}
'''José Narro Robles''' (born December 5, 1948 in [[Saltillo, Coahuila]]) is a [[Mexico|Mexican]] researcher, academic, and politician. He is a former director of the [[School of Medicine, UNAM|Faculty of Medicine]] of the [[National Autonomous University of Mexico]] (UNAM) and was elected its 23rd [[Rector (academia)|Rector]] on November 20, 2007.<ref name="jornada"> {{cite web | author = La Jornada | date = 2007-11-13 | title = José Narro Robles; la UNAM tiene nuevo rector | url = http://www.jornada.unam.mx/ultimas/2007/11/13/designan-a-jose-narro-robles-nuevo-rector-de-la-unam | language = Spanish | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20071115150206/http://www.jornada.unam.mx/ultimas/2007/11/13/designan-a-jose-narro-robles-nuevo-rector-de-la-unam | archivedate = 2007-11-15 | df = }} </ref> After two 4-year periods leading UNAM, in February 2016, he was appointed by Mexican President [[Enrique Peña Nieto]] to replace [[Mercedes Juan López|Mercedes Juan]] as head of the Mexican [[Secretariat of Health (Mexico)|Secretariat of Health]].<ref>{{cite news|work=Animal Político|date=2016-02-08|accessdate=2016-02-08|url=http://www.animalpolitico.com/2016/02/cambios-en-el-gabinete-de-pena-emilio-lozoya-deja-la-direccion-de-pemex/|title=Cambios en el gabinete de Peña: Nuevos titulares de Pemex, IMSS y la Secretaría de Salud|language=Spanish}}</ref>
Robles has enacted as adviser for the [[World Health Organization]], [[WHO]] and [[UNICEF]]. He has been president of the [[National Academy of Medicine (Mexico)|National Academy of Medicine]], of which he has been a member since 1992.<ref name="jornada" /> He has also worked as General Director of Health Services of the [[Mexican Federal District]], Secretary-General of the [[Mexican Institute of Social Security]] (IMSS), Undersecretary of Migratory Services and Population at the Ministry of the Interior (''Secretaría de Gobernación'') and Undersecretary of Health at the Federal Secretariat of Health.<ref name="ElUniversal">{{cite web| |author = El Universal |title = Semblanza: José Narro Robles|url = http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/notas/461141.html|date = 2007-11-13|language = Spanish}}</ref> He holds a number of honorary doctorates from Latin American and European universities.
==Honorary doctorates== *[[University of Birmingham]], [[United Kingdom]], (2012). <ref name="doctorado">{{cite journal |title=Gaceta UNAM |year=2012 |number=4 476 |issn=0188-5138 |url=http://www.dgcs.unam.mx/gacetaweb/2012/121206/gaceta.pdf}}. Gaceta UNAM, 6 de diciembre de 2012, página 7, cita a Cristóbal López.</ref> *[[Universidad de Santiago de Chile]] , [[Chile]] (2017), <ref name="doctoradosant">{{cite journal |title=Doctorado Honoris Causa, Santiago de Chile |year=2017 |url=http://eleconomista.com.mx/sociedad/2017/07/03/jose-narro-recibe-doctorado-honoris-causa-santiago}}</ref> *[[Universidad de la Habana]], [[Cuba]], (2016). <ref>{{cite journal |title=Desplegado Oficial Universidad de la Habana, Cuba |url=http://www.uh.cu/node/3385}} </ref> *[[Universidad Juárez Autónoma de Tabasco]] (2011).<ref>{{cite journal |title=Gaceta UNAM |year=2011 |number=4 320 |issn=0188-5138 |url=http://www.dgcs.unam.mx/gacetaweb/2011/110314/gaceta.pdf}} </ref> *[[Universidad de Salamanca]], [[Spain]] (2016). <ref name="discurso">{{cite journal |title=Discurso Salamanca, Doctorado Honoris Causa |year=2016 |url=http://www.jornada.unam.mx/ultimas/2016/04/05/discurso-integro-de-jose-narro-robles-al-recibir-el-doctorado-honoris-causa}}</ref> *[[Universidad Autónoma de Campeche]], [[México]], (2015) <ref name="doctoradoucamp">{{cite journal |title=Doctorado Honoris Causa, Universidad de Campeche |year=2015 |url=http://www.gaceta.unam.mx/20150622/doctorado-honoris-causa-de-la-uac-a-jose-narro/}}</ref> *[[Benemérita Universidad Autónoma de Puebla]] ([[BUAP]]), [[México]], (2013) *[[Universidad Autónoma de Sinaloa]], [[México]], ((2015). *[[Universidad Autónoma de San Luis Potosí]] ([[UASLP]]), [[México]], 2015. *[[Universidad Autónoma de Nuevo León]] ([[UANL]]), [[México]], (2016).<ref>{{cite journal| title= Comunicado UANL| year=2016| url=http://www.uanl.mx/noticias/institucional/reconoce-uanl-intelectuales-educadores-y-humanistas.html}} </ref>
